watermark.note: Beehive surrounded by flying bees (Tumba bruk).

collation.catchwords: Catchwords in black ink in black and brown frames.

p.note: Middle of the page in brown ink by an early-modern hand: Legenda Sanctorum compilata a Jacobo a Voragine nacione Januensi, de ordine fratrum Predicatorum..

binding.p: Medieval binding. Brown leather over wooden boards. 5 pairs of raised bands and 2 endbands. , top of page, half of a medieval parchment lable with nails in it, text in black ink: legenda. , ink on paper label: N:o 21. Jac. Jannensis Legenda aurea Sanctorum; stamped in gold: A 158; ink on paper label: e. 30. 6. 13.
The endleaves consist of 2 bifolia from Petrus Comestor’s Historia scholastica. These fragments seem to be written by the same or a similar hand as the main text
binding.condition: Leather heavily torn. Board visible on . Remains of clasps (nails on ), corner and centre pieces. Wormholes all over covers. New leather added to

history.provenance: The manuscript is listed in Vossius’s catalogue from 1649 (U 202:1) and has belonged to the National Library since. It probably came to Sweden as war booty or was bought on the continent by Queen Christina. There are 3 signa on the . The older signum 21 is found in the catalogue from 1734 (U 125e); e. 30.6.13. is found in Hammarsköld’s catalogue from the 19th century (U 133); A 158 (current signum).

supportDesc.foliation: Chapter headings in red ink in top margin.
supportDesc.condition: Holes in parchment, e.g. on , but no loss of text. Parchment repaired, e.g. on . Some leaves show signs of having been folded in the corners. : piece of the leaf cut out. , Inner marign, bottom: plant remains, or scraps of wood.

p.note: Mariginal additions by several different hands from different periods in the form of manicules, signs, corrections, and comments. The additions are not very frequent and usually only consist of one word. Many of the corrections appear to be by the scribe or a contemporary hand.

decoDesc.p: Main text in black ink, capitals touched in yellow, rubrics in red.
decoDesc.decoNote: : Foliate initial U over 7 lines (+ extending in the margin). The letter is placed in a blue frame with gold edges, the counter space is gilded and filled with a curled vegetative shape with two leaves and fox’s (?) head. Part of the frame or letter extends along the inner margin and half of the bottom margin. Main colours pink, blue, and red. The inital is followed by a smaller capital penwork N over 2 lines in black and touched in yellow. : plain initals over 2-3 lines in blue or red with red, blue and/or green flourishing, which sometimes extends along the entire margin. The initial is followed by a capital touched in yellow, occasionally these capitals inlcude some penwork details, e.g. .
